Horace speaks with the independence os a man who knows his own mind and his own value. The intimacy with Maecenas had led to a friendship hardly less close with Augustus, who wished to attach Horace to his household as secretary ¹. The poet, however, declined this confidential position and remained simply his prince’s favourite guest. ln 17 B.c. a great occasion gave him official recognition as laureate. Augustus determined to revive the ludi saeculares or centennial games, observance of which had lapsed. It was in a sense the jubilee of the principate‚ now fairly and firmly established as a reign of peace and good order after a century of war and anarchy: and a central feature of the games was the great hymn to Phoebus and Diana written by Horace, and sung under his direction by a chorus of boys
